        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer mt-4 text-gray-600 text-base hidden">
          You can upload any screen recording, product walkthrough, or user journey video in MP4, GIF, or Loom format. The video should showcase the flow or feature you want to analyze.
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow p-6">
        <button type="button" class="w-full flex justify-between items-center text-left faq-toggle font-semibold text-gray-900 text-lg">
          How does the AI detect UX issues?
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer mt-4 text-gray-600 text-base hidden">
          Our AI analyzes your video to detect user interactions, interface elements, and potential points of friction. It's trained on thousands of UX best practices and can identify usability issues like confusing navigation, form issues, and conversion blockers.
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow p-6">
        <button type="button" class="w-full flex justify-between items-center text-left faq-toggle font-semibold text-gray-900 text-lg">
          How long does the analysis take?
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer mt-4 text-gray-600 text-base hidden">
          Most analyses are completed within minutes, depending on the length and complexity of your video. You'll receive a notification when your UX report is ready.
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow p-6">
        <button type="button" class="w-full flex justify-between items-center text-left faq-toggle font-semibold text-gray-900 text-lg">
          Is my product data and video secure?
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer mt-4 text-gray-600 text-base hidden">
          Yes, we take security seriously. Your videos are analyzed securely and never shared with third parties. All uploaded content is automatically deleted after 30 days, or you can delete it manually at any time.
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- FAQ Item 5 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow p-6">
        <button type="button" class="w-full flex justify-between items-center text-left faq-toggle font-semibold text-gray-900 text-lg">
          Do I need technical knowledge to implement the suggestions?
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer mt-4 text-gray-600 text-base hidden">
          No, our suggestions are designed to be clear and actionable for both designers and non-designers. We provide visual examples and specific recommendations that you can easily share with your team.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <script>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
      const toggles = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-toggle');
      const answers = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-answer');
      const icons = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-toggle svg');
      toggles.forEach((toggle, idx) => {
        toggle.addEventListener('click', function() {
          answers.forEach((ans, i) => {
            if (i === idx) {
              ans.classList.toggle('hidden');
              icons[i].classList.toggle('rotate-180');
            } else {
              ans.classList.add('hidden');
              icons[i].classList.remove('rotate-180');
            }
          });
        });
      });
    });
  </script>
</section>

